    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nHi there!\n\nAn error message shows when trying to look at document symbols using python-lsp-server:\n```\nvim.schedule callback: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/util.lua:1955: attempt to concatenate field 'containerName' (a userdata value)\nstack traceback:\n        /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/util.lua:1955: in function 'map_result'\n        /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/handlers.lua:294: in function 'handler'\n        /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/buf.lua:180: in function 'handler'\n        /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/client.lua:742: in function ''\n        vim/_core/editor.lua: in function <vim/_core/editor.lua:0>\n```\n\nThis does not happen with any other LSP I've used recently.\n\nThe error is thrown in `vim.lsp.util.symbols_to_items()` when `symbol.containerName` is `vim.NIL`:\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/43398547ec72c99ab0b90837c02de4a0add77b04/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/util.lua#L1972\n\nProbably related to this change in 0.12:\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/43398547ec72c99ab0b90837c02de4a0add77b04/runtime/doc/news.txt#L54-L55\n\nI guess the fix is to check explicitly for `vim.NIL` instead of using the ternary operator. I don't have the time right now to familiarise myself with how to contribute that change myself but I hope this helps!\n\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim --clean -u minimal_init.lua\"\n\n```lua\n-- minimal_init.lua\nlocal pattern = \"python\"\nlocal cmd = { \"pylsp\" }\nlocal root_markers = { \".git\", \".editorconfig\" }\nlocal settings = vim.empty_dict()\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"FileType\", {\n\tpattern = pattern,\n\tcallback = function(args)\n\t\tlocal match = vim.fs.find(root_markers, { path = args.file, upward = true })[1]\n\t\tlocal root_dir = match and vim.fn.fnamemodify(match, \":p:h\") or nil\n\t\tvim.lsp.start({\n\t\t\tname = \"pylsp\",\n\t\t\tcmd = cmd,\n\t\t\troot_dir = root_dir,\n\t\t\tsettings = settings,\n\t\t})\n\tend,\n})\n\nvim.lsp.set_log_level(\"debug\")\n```\n\n1. Open Neovim `nvim --clean -u minimal_init.lua`.\n2. Open an empty python file `:e test.py`.\n3. Query document symbols `gO`.\n4. Observe \"No document symbols found\".\n5. Add code to the python file `import os`.\n6. Query document symbols `gO`.\n7. Observe the error message as above.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIt should display the symbols as expected.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.1\n\n### Language server name/version\n\npython-lsp-server 1.14.0-2\n\n### Operating system/version\n\narch linux\n\n### Log file\n\nhttps://gist.github.com/mariusz-tang/78d362b2d7a2372469db6de9c1b32303",
